OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FAfter a chilly start with
OL,6,Fovernight frost it will be another dry
OL,7,Fand bright day with long spells of
OL,8,Fsunshine, though some western areas
OL,9,Fstarting cloudier.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FA dry evening with patchy
OL,12,Fcloud and largely clear skies.
OL,13,FRemaining dry with clear spells
OL,14,Fovernight, leading to a touch of frost
OL,15,Fin places.
OL,16,
OL,17,CSunday:FA dry morning with sunny
OL,18,Fspells. Remaining dry through the
OL,19,Fafternoon and turning cloudier, but
OL,20,Fstill some bright or sunny intervals
OL,21,Fbreaking through.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
